  "dataset": "CIC-IDS2017",
  "headline_split": "cross-capture (train Mon/Tue/Wed, test Thu/Fri)",
  "why": "The random per-family split scored 99.8% recall, but the CSVs carry no timestamp so near-duplicate flows from one attack burst cannot be kept on one side of it. Testing on entirely unseen captures is the honest measure of whether the model generalises to behaviour it was not trained on.",
